	(234, '38', '', 'a.   Badan Informasi Geospasial (BIG)', '29', 2018, 'The Accelerate Program of One Map Policy Implemmentation/ Program to Accelerate Agrarian Reform', 'The Accelerate Program of One Map Policy Implemmentation/ Program to Accelerate Agrarian Reform', 'a. 	Component 1- Development of the National Spatial Data Infrastructure; This component  has three (3) sub-components, including:\r\ni. Densification  and  quality  improvement of  Geodetic  Control   Network   (Vertical  and\r\nHorizontal);\r\nii.  Improvement of content and quality of spatial data in the National Spatial Data Network\r\nGaringan Data Spasial National-JSDN);\r\niii.  Capacity and utilization including  the National Spatial Data Network Systems and inter­ sectoral  dashboard   for  senior  officials, and  public  access  to  geospatial   information through  the Geoportal;\r\n\r\nb. 	Component 2 - Development  of National  Land Spatial  Data and  land  use demarcation at village level.\r\n\r\ni. Quality improvement of spatial data for national land management;\r\nii. Acceleration of land base mapping and national land registry;\r\niii. Verification and  land  use data synchronization at village level, particularly in priority', 'a. 	Component 1- Development of the National Spatial Data Infrastructure; This component  has three (3) sub-components, including:\r\ni. Densification  and  quality  improvement of  Geodetic  Control   Network   (Vertical  and\r\nHorizontal);\r\nii.  Improvement of content and quality of spatial data in the National Spatial Data Network\r\nGaringan Data Spasial National-JSDN);\r\niii.  Capacity and utilization including  the National Spatial Data Network Systems and inter­ sectoral  dashboard   for  senior  officials, and  public  access  to  geospatial   information through  the Geoportal;\r\n\r\nb. 	Component 2 - Development  of National  Land Spatial  Data and  land  use demarcation at village level.\r\n\r\ni. Quality improvement of spatial data for national land management;\r\nii. Acceleration of land base mapping and national land registry;\r\niii. Verification and  land  use data synchronization at village level, particularly in priority', 200000000, 0, 2015, 48, '1.   Component 1:\r\ni.	Densification of the vertical control network as much as 200 points, and horizontal control networks as much as 150 points;\r\nii. 	Provision of digital geospatial base information equivalent  of 500 sheets of of national base map coverage at scales of 1: 50,000 and 1: 5,000\r\niii. 	Compilation of thematic digital geospatial information  of sectoral data and areas for major themes that are needed in the development of priority areas equivalent to 1,500 sheets of map coverage at scales of 1:50,000 to 1: 25,000\r\niv. 	Improvement of human resources capacity of up-to 500 personnel;\r\n\r\n2. 	Component 2:\r\ni.	Improvements to the quality of spatial data covering 23,000 priority villages for land sector;\r\nii. 	Land use and land parcels boundary deliniation through  participatory process in as many as 23,000 villages in 12 priority provinces prone to forest fires and associated land use conflicts\r\niii. 	Increasing the capacity of human resources for the verification and synchronization of boundary at the village level for up to 1,500 people', '1.  Availability  of system for the provision  and updating of geospatial  data with national coverage  at  a scale  of 1: 50,000 that  fulfil  the  definition,  structure and  operational criteria  of "One Map" for the development planning  process  to achieve the target  of Nawacita through  holistic-thematic, integrative, and spatial approach.\r\n2.  Establishment  of data  exchange  mechanism  among  agencies  and  local governments within the framework  of open data through  the National Spatial Data Network  (JDSN) for development planning process.\r\n3.  Increased effectiveness and certainty of the economic and social development program as a positive  impact  on the  transparency an