	(235, '53', '', 'Deputillmu Pengetahuan Kebumian LIPI', '33', 2017, 'Procurement Multi Purposes Research Vessel', 'Procurement Multi Purposes Research Vessel', 'a. Preparation and Development of Technical Design\r\nThe preparation  activities  are started  with  data collection of the  types of  surveys that expected to be conducted and scientific equipment which should be installed on the ship. This activity is carried out by using the FGD method with invited the researchers from LIPI and other research institutions  as potential users of research vessels as well as other key stakeholders. Then it followed by development of technical design of the proposed vessel. The development  of technical design will be conducted by the experienced consultant in multi purposes research vessel building.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nb. The construction of vessel and installment of scientific instrument\r\nThe multi  purposes research vessel requires  the  very  special conditions  that  are  not necessary in the goods or passengers vessels, such as vibration and noise levels. It is due to the  mounted  scientific instrument  in the vessel that  has intensive high technology. The multi-purposes  research vessel has a  very  high complexity  compared  to  the  freighter, tankers and passenger ships.\r\n\r\nBased on  experience  and  the  information   obtained, currently  there  is no  shipyard  in Indonesia  capable  in  producing  a  multi-purposes  research  vessel  with   high  quality standards. Indeed, today there  are several shipyards in Indonesia has successfully built several research vessel for the Indonesian government, but limited to the research vessels with have similar functions only.\r\n\r\nThe process of technology transfer on the multi-purposes research vessel building should be performed. Therefore, it is proposed in this project that the construction of two units of the vessels is divided in two schemes. One unit of vessel is built in foreign shipyard that have high competence and the other vessel (sister ship) built in the Indonesian shipyard, with a note that it is necessary for the foreign shipyard to conduct technology transfer the selected Indonesian shipyard. The procurement process of ship building contractor will be based on the applicable regulations in Indonesia, the world trade rules, and based on the agreements with the donors.\r\n\r\nThe research instrument  that mounted on board reflects the types of surveys that can be carried by the  vessel. The scientific equipment  should serve the  surveys of physics and chemicals oceanography; bottom  bathymetry; marine geology; seismic; marine biology and fisheries.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n8\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\'I\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\nc. Supervision of Vessel Construction\r\nDuring the construction and the installation of research instrument will be supervised by the\r\nIndonesian Consultants both government and private agencies.\r\n\r\n\r\nd. Training and Familiarization\r\nThe activities of training and familiarization of the vessel and research instrument  will be given to the crew, technicians/ operators and researchers who will be assigned to operate the vessel and research equipment.\r\n\r\n\r\ne. Testing,Commissioning and Handover\r\nBefore conducting the handover of the vessel, the shipyard is required to conduct some testing on the ship that have been built and all the equipment that were mounted on it.', 'a. Preparation and Development of Technical Design\r\nThe preparation  activities  are started  with  data collection of the  types of  surveys that expected to be conducted and scientific equipment which should be installed on the ship. This activity is carried out by using the FGD method with invited the researchers from LIPI and other research institutions  as potential users of research vessels as well as other key stakeholders. Then it followed by development of technical design of the proposed vessel. The development  of technical design will be conducted b